Rebecca Ejifoma In its fight against the COVID-19, Natures Gentle Touch has unveiled a new range of hand wash products into the market. According to the General Manager, Natures Gentle Touch, Mr. Chijioke Anaele, to combat COVID-19, the company acknowledges that “safety lies in the hands; hence, the need for proper washing under running water or sanitising hands when there is no water and soap”. The new products, he listed, come in three variants: Coconut, Aloe Vera, and Ocean Breeze. He emphasised that the products cleanse, moisturise, and refresh the hands. “In 2011, the company introduced Herbalblend Anti- Bacterial Hand Sanitizer, specifically designed to instantly cleanse hands and kill 99.9% of germs, without water,” he recalled. Anaele further highlighted that Natures Gentle Touch Hand Wash and Hand Sanitisers can be used anytime, anywhere. “It can be use while in the cars, offices, handbag, picnics, nappy change, travel, and sports among others,” he outlined. The GM further urged Nigerians to continue to follow the guidelines given by health officials, and ensure frequent sanitising, washing of hands, and social distancing to effectively fight the pandemic. Introduced in 1997, Natures Gentle Touch is a personal style brand that uses scientific approach and natural ingredients to provide hair, scalp, hygiene and beauty care solutions.